Officially on cycle 3 trying to get pregnant with our double rainbow baby! 🤍 Anyone else ttc? I have been using @naturalcycles and am IN LOVE!! It is the first ever FDA cleared birth control app. Natural Cycles was developed by scientists & it does more than just track your cycle. Using your body temperature and other fertility indicators, its unique algorithm tells you whether you’re fertile or not fertile, so you can plan accordingly. I’m trying to get pregnant so it’s important I know my fertile days, which the app narrows down for me! When we are finally blessed with baby #4, I will continue to use Natural Cycles to prevent another pregnancy because it is a non hormonal & non invasive option. It is 98% effective with perfect use (perfect use = no unprotected sex on red days) and 93% effective with typical use.The best part? I have a code for you! Go to Naturalcycles.com and use my code SKYE to get a free thermometer and 20% off your annual subscription! * NC° is for 18+ and does not protect against STIs AD

walking into 2023 feeling all the emotions 🤍 2022 brought alot of hurt but even more blessings. We spent 713 hours outside making memories, we traveled a lot, roamy quit breastfeeding, we bought our first house, i got pregnant and miscarried twice, roamy got a 3rd degree burn, hugh broke his toe, our kids all grew & learned so incredibly much, we learned how to can & bake our own bread, my husband celebrated 1 year of being a stay at home dad, I doubled our income (thanks to each and everyone of you who support our family) but most importantly, we are living a life we could only dream about a few years ago. ☁️ If I could buy one thing in this new year, it would be time 🤍

I love them snow much 🫶❄️ we didn’t reach our 1000 hours outside goal last year so we are trying again. I think it’s important to remember that the biggest goal should be being intentional with getting outdoors & making memories. It shouldn’t be stressful trying to reach 1000 hours (or whatever your goal may be) It should be a positive experience for all of you. Today I made a snow angel for the first time in years, I ate the snow with my kids & we just sat there laughing with eachother. 
Bundling them is stressful, sometimes there’s big meltdowns & in those moments I wonder why I’m pushing us to get outside? It would be so much easier to just stay inside on these days. but my mental health increases, their mood improves & we feel more connected. 🤍

becoming a family of 6 has given me so much already 🤍
so much more love. understanding. patience. surrendering to the stage of motherhood I’m in, and finding calm in the chaos has been such a breath of fresh air 🫶🏻🌷🧺

nobody talks about how guilty you’ll feel when you get your rainbow baby. those sleepless nights you prayed so hard for. the changing diapers you hoped for. the cluster feeding you wished for. and now you’re in that season of life, while so many others are still waiting. those who deserve it just as much as you. those who have spent even more years, who have experienced even more heartbreak. it’s so unfair to think about sometimes. October is pregnancy and infant loss awareness month. If you’re ttc, grieving, waiting, etc, I see you 🤍✨

breakfast for my 5(ish) kids 😉🫶🏻 Baked oatmeal, cantaloupe & a beef stick. 
BAKED CINNAMON ROLL OATMEAL RECIPE-
in a large bowl whisk together..
2 eggs
1 cup milk
5 tablespoons melted butter
1/4 cup maple syrup
1/4 cup brown sugar 
2 tsp vanilla extract 
Stir in:
3 cups oats
2 tsp baking powder
1 tbsp cinnamon
Let mixture sit for 10 minutes while oven preheats to 350 & you grease a 9x13 pan.
Bake for 25 minutes!
mix 1/2 cup powdered sugar & 2 tbsp milk for the glaze to add on top! inspired by the gorgeous @christaceliaa to start sharing some of our meals ✨
ENJOYYY 🤍 #momsofinstagram #breakfastideas #motherhood #mealideas #momof4 #postpartum

I took “before” pictures today. Not even realizing these are also my AFTER pictures. I just spent 9 beautiful months being home to my 4th baby 🤍 why is it, once the 6 weeks is up, we no longer give our bodies grace? We are still postpartum. Our bodies just grew and changed tremendously for 9 entire months. for 9 months we stretched & grew in a million ways to nourish a tiny human ✨ THAT is the most amazing journey. THIS BODY is worth celebrating just as much as my “goal” weight or body. 🫶🏻 Just your friendly reminder that your body is the least interesting thing about you. going into my health journey with this mindset might be the best thing for me. I am ready to feel good, and take care of myself for my babies and my future 🤎

One of the best things I did while pregnant was take @thegenatetest 🙌🏻 I was able to learn about my genetics & how I process nutrients that are vital to babies development! My biggest struggle is choline. And turns out, most prenatals on the market don’t contain any despite the importance it has on cognitive development. Even though it’s a prenatal nutrition test, this is amazing through all stages of motherhood, including postpartum! After meeting with the nutritionist & increasing my choline intake I’ve noticed a huge improvement in wakefulness and energy levels. So thankful for the knowledge I’ve gained with Genate. #momsofinstagram #motherhood #pregnancy #postpartum

if you have a goal to learn how to make bread- this recipe is AMAZING!!! so simple and tasty 🫶🏻 combine 2 cups warm water, 1. tablespoon dry active yeast with 1/4 cup honey. Let that get bubbly. add in 3 tablespoons melted butter, 2 tsp salt, and 4.5 cups flour. mix/knead until well combined then add in an additional 1/2 cup flour. Mix again. Let rise for one hour, I put mine in the oven with the light on. Shape your bread then rise for another hour. bake at 350 for 30 minutes! heads up- if you’re planning to give to your kids under a year old, you will want to substitute the honey. #momsofinstagram #homemadebread #motherhood #homemaking
